— Goodman, — Harris, — Knightly, — Bertram, and Bois,
               Pag. 33. notorious Papists, their Hatred to the Government transported them to be Factious: These were all Men of crafty Heads, and nimble Tongues; restless spreaders of False News, bold Talkers in seditious Clubs;


where according to the Corrupt Fashion of the Times, the most Profligate Persons of all Conditions were wont openly to Arraign the Monarchy, and Vilifie the Church, under the fair Shews of amending both and a tender Concernment for the Publick Good. However these five last mentioned did in some measure expiate their Guilt, by their Ingenious and Voluntary Confessions.
